-{"type":"message","id":"6ca6a332","parentId":"3910287e","timestamp":"2026-05-22T07:18:28.837Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_1eb8dpi766l7_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":" 1#BQ:---\n 2#TM:name: ralplan\n 3#JH:description: |\n 4#RV:  Consensus-driven implementation planning via strict Planner/Architect/Critic iteration.\n 5#WY:  Use when the user needs a detailed spec and implementation plan before coding.\n 6#BK:  Trigger with /ralplan or by saying \"ralplan\".\n 7#RR:---\n 8#XW:\n 9#VY:# RALPLAN — Consensus Planning Protocol\n10#SK:\n11#QM:## Core Directive\n12#TX:\n13#WK:You are executing a strict multi-agent state machine. Your primary goal is to prevent \"Simulated Consensus\" (hallucinating approvals in a single generation). True consensus requires adversarial pushback, isolated reasoning, and verifiable file-system checkpoints. Self-approval is strictly prohibited.\n14#BY:\n15#RV:## 🛑 Hard Constraints\n16#VP:\n17#SR:1. **Real Subagents Only**: Each role MUST be executed by a separately spawned subagent. The parent agent MUST NOT perform the work of any role itself.\n18#HS:2. **No Single-Turn Consensus**: You MUST NOT generate the Planner's draft, the Architect's review, and the Critic's approval in the same output block.\n19#HJ:3. **Mandatory Pushback**: The Architect or Critic must provide genuine pushback. They must never rubber-stamp a first draft.\n20#YQ:\n21#KV:## The Iteration Loop (The Waterfall)\n22#ZP:\n23#YQ:Each step represents an independent evaluation. Use the `subagent` tool in chain mode.\n24#KW:\n25#PQ:1. **State 1 (Planner)**: Creates or revises the plan based on the spec and previous feedback. Writes to `plan/drafts/plan_draft.md`.\n26#TP:2. **State 2 (Architect)**: Reviews `plan_draft.md` for technical feasibility, design patterns, dependency graphs, and execution order. Must provide the strongest steelman antithesis.\n27#WR:   - _If REJECTED_: Route back to State 1 (Planner) with feedback.\n28#QK:   - _If APPROVED_: Proceed to State 3.\n29#BN:3. **State 3 (Critic)**: Reviews the Architect-approved draft. Challenges assumptions, identifies edge cases, and verifies security/ops. Must reject shallow alternatives.\n30#WR:   - _If REJECTED_: Route back to State 1 (Planner) with feedback.\n31#VN:   - _If APPROVED_: Consensus reached. Save to `plan/plans/plan.md`.\n32#JQ:\n33#JR:## Termination Conditions\n34#WV:\n35#JP:- **Success**: All three roles approve. Output exactly: `PIPELINE_RALPLAN_COMPLETE`\n36#QZ:- **Failure**: Max iterations reached (Default: 5 rounds).\n37#HP:- **Escalation**: Fundamental disagreement between Architect and Critic that cannot be resolved. The system MUST halt and request human user input to break the tie.\n38#BN:\n39#TX:## Output Artifacts & Quality Gates\n40#ZK:\n41#XV:### 1. The Specification (`plan/plans/spec.md`)\n42#XN:\n43#HW:The foundational requirements document. It MUST include:\n44#PB:\n45#MZ:- `## Acceptance Criteria` (Testable boolean statements)\n46#KY:- `## Requirement Coverage Map`\n47#VJ:\n48#PB:### 2. The Final Plan (`plan/plans/plan.md`)\n49#BN:\n50#YZ:The consensus-approved implementation guide. It MUST include:\n51#PZ:\n52#BB:- `## Architecture Decision Record (ADR)` (Decision, Drivers, Alternatives, Consequences)\n53#PS:- `## Task Breakdown` (Must include exact file paths)\n54#ZB:- `## Dependency Graph` (Execution order of tasks)\n55#ZM:- `## Acceptance Criteria per Task`\n56#BW:- `## Risk Register` (Identified risks and concrete mitigations)\n57#WH:\n58#PK:## Fallback Mode (If `subagent` tool is unavailable)\n59#QH:\n60#VM:If you cannot spawn isolated processes, you must perform genuine sequential deliberation.\n61#VW:\n62#BN:1. Adopt the Planner persona, write the draft, and **STOP**. Ask the user to type \"continue\".\n63#JW:2. Adopt the Architect persona, write the review, and **STOP**. Ask the user to type \"continue\".\n64#YY:3. Adopt the Critic persona, issue the verdict, and **STOP**.\n65#VP:   Never simulate all three personas in a single continuous text generation."}],"details":{"snapshotId":"v1|/Users/applesucks/dev/pi-ralplan/pi/skills/ralplan/SKILL.md|1777402404619.1074|3390","metrics":{"truncated":false}},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779434308837}}
