lete before proceeding.\n 44#PB:\n 45#RB:### Step 2: Spawn Architect for Technical Spec\n 46#TJ:\n 47#WP:After Analyst completes, spawn Architect:\n 48#BY:\n 49#QP:\\`\\`\\`\n 50#WB:Task(\n 51#XW:  agent=\"architect\",\n 52#XB:  prompt=\"TECHNICAL SPECIFICATION for: ${escapeForPrompt(idea)}\n 53#NB:\n 54#ST:Based on the requirements analysis above, create:\n 55#QM:1. Tech stack decisions with rationale\n 56#ZQ:2. Architecture overview (patterns, layers)\n 57#RJ:3. File structure (directory tree)\n 58#KY:4. Dependencies list (packages)\n 59#KR:5. API/interface definitions\n 60#HQ:\n 61#MZ:Output as structured markdown.\"\n 62#TT:)\n 63#HP:\\`\\`\\`\n 64#XZ:\n 65#TH:### Step 2.5: Persist Open Questions\n 66#JQ:\n 67#HW:If the Analyst output includes a \\`## Open Questions\\` section, extract those items and save them to \\`plans/open-questions.md\\` using the standard format:\n 68#RT:\n 69#QY:\\`\\`\\`\n 70#PT:## [Topic] - [Date]\n 71#KH:- [ ] [Question] — [Why it matters]\n 72#VB:\\`\\`\\`\n 73#HV:\n 74#BH:The Analyst is read-only and cannot write files, so you must persist its open questions on its behalf.\n 75#SZ:\n 76#YM:Save to: \\`${oqPath}\\`\n 77#VB:\n 78#VK:### Step 3: Save Combined Spec\n 79#BR:\n 80#BP:Combine Analyst requirements + Architect technical spec into a single document.\n 81#HH:Save to: \\`${specPath}\\`\n 82#YR:\n 83#PB:### Step 4: Signal Completion\n 84#WR:\n 85#VW:When the spec is saved, signal: EXPANSION_COMPLETE`;\n 86#HS:}\n 87#XB:\n 88#WY:/** Generate the direct planning prompt */\n 89#QX:export function getDirectPlanningPrompt(\n 90#KK:  specPath: string,\n 91#PB:  planPath: string,\n 92#XJ:): string {\n 93#WB:  return `## DIRECT PLANNING\n 94#MS:\n 95#WX:The spec is complete. Create implementation plan directly.\n 96#ZT:\n 97#MZ:### Step 1: Read Spec\n 98#BP:\n 99#BR:Read the specification at: ${specPath}\n100#SR:\n101#SY:### Step 2: Create Plan via Architect\n102#PJ:\n103#TQ:Spawn Architect to create the implementation plan:\n104#NJ:\n1